DefaultMessage.SourceString: Welcome back, agent. I need you to focus on <enemy>Sunny.</>

Listen up. Your mission is to infiltrate <enemy>Believer Beach.</>
Find the ringleader and <b>win them over</>
We just had a <b>major</> IO security breach.
I need to investigate, but I <b>can't let anyone know</> I'm aware of what happened.
Find me a <enemy>Field Team access card. </>
Do <b>whatever</> needs to be done.
All of <b>our lives</> depend on you finding that <enemy>card. </>
We still have a <b>significant</> lack of knowledge about the alien invasion force.
Knowledge isn't just power here... knowledge is <b>survival</>.
We'll start by monitoring their activities on the Island.
Then we turn our attention to the <b>mothership</>.
Uh-- Why don't you start by looking into those <enemy>strange billboards</>?
<enemy>The abduction situation</> is hitting a <b>crisis point. </> We need to get a handle on it yesterday.
The rate of alien abductions is <b>far above</> expectations.
This isn't just for study.
It's like they want to abduct everyone at least once.
We need to know why.
Learn everything you can about the abductions
The why. The how. The who. And try not to get abducted too many times...
It's probably not great for your brain.
Peaceful solutions are still in play, but don't hold your breath.
We need to prepare for the worst. And I do mean <b>the worst</>.
The IO does have a counter attack plan in place, but I believe it's been compromised.

<b>Earn his trust</> and learn 
everything you can.
This level of alien support <enemy>isn't natural</>
You and me are creating a <b>backup plan</>.
Start with <enemy>weapons testing</>.
I'll handle the behind-the-scenes work.
Try to squeeze any useful intel from them. If you can recruit them, even better.
There's an alien in quote-unquote "<b>deep cover</>."
I'm hitting a dead end. We need an asset on the inside.
I think she may be behind the uptick in <b>anti-human sentiment</> on the Island.

All I know about her is that she's a big fan of that radio show, uh...
<b> "Hot Saucers."</>

Catch up on the show. Learn the lingo. 
<b>Earn her trust.</>

We need a boots-on-the-ground presence on <b>Hayseed's farm.</>  
We need him <b>alive and on our side. </>

Maybe you could 
<b>bribe him with some supplies.</>
The guy's a bit of a hoarder.
